'''大桃子'''（英語：{{lang|en|Peachoid}}）是一座桃子外形、高{{convert|135|ft}}、位于[[加夫尼_(南卡羅來納州)|美國南卡羅來納州加夫尼市]]的[[水塔|水塔]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emporis.com/building/peachoidwatertower-gaffney-sc-usa|title=Peachoid Water Tower|publisher=[[Emporis|Emporis]]|accessdate=2 August 2013|archive-date=2013-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224121320/http://www.emporis.com/building/peachoidwatertower-gaffney-sc-usa|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

大桃子的容積是一百萬美式[[加侖|加侖]]，約三百八十萬公升。它坐落于大桃子路旁{{link-en|南卡85號州际公路|Interstate 85 in South Carolina}}的90號和92號出口之間。當地人稱其爲“桃子”“加夫尼大月亮”。從數英里遠處就可看到其樣子。<ref name="PeachoidRoadside">{{cite web|url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/story/2213|title=Peachoid Water Tower, Gaffney, South Carolina|publisher=Roadside America|accessdate=2015-11-20|archive-date=2015-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151128095204/http://www.roadsideamerica.com/story/2213|dead-url=no}}</ref>

作爲{{link-en|新奇建築|Novelty architecture}}，大桃子已成爲85號州际公路上最爲矚目的[[地標|地標]]。

==歷史==
大桃子由{{link-en|芝加哥橋梁鋼鐵公司|Chicago Bridge and Iron Company}}在1981年建成，主要建材爲鋼筋混凝土。<ref name="BigPeachClanton" />枝幹和葉片爲附著在實際建築物表面的裝飾，巨大的桃子中縫由金屬板材加工而成。建築的上色和細節則由畫家彼得・弗罗伊登贝格完成。

加夫尼公共设施局为了使用联邦资金建造水塔而委托建造大桃子。<ref name="PeachoidRoadside" />之所以选择桃子的外形，是因为当地桃农是加夫尼的经济的重要组成部分，而且加夫尼所属的[[切羅基縣_(南卡羅萊納州)|切羅基縣]]曾经一度出产过比整个佐治亚州还多的桃子。<ref name="PeachoidRoadside" />建成以来，大桃子的超高可见度使得旅游成为当地经济的组成部分。<ref name="PostandCourier">{{cite news | url = http://www.postandcourier.com/article/20130319/PC16/130319226 | title = Upstate town’s giant peach is ripe for fame on Netflix drama 'House of Cards' | author = Stephen Largen | date = 19 March 2013 | accessdate = 22 February 2014 | newspaper = [[The_Post_and_Courier|The Post and Courier]] | location = [[Charleston,_South_Carolina|Charleston, South Carolina]] | archive-date = 2015-12-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151222121116/http://www.postandcourier.com/article/20130319/PC16/130319226 | dead-url = no }}</ref>

一个小号的大桃子（50万美式加仑，190万公升）由同一公司在[[阿拉巴馬州|阿拉巴馬州]][[克蘭頓_(阿拉巴馬州)|克蘭頓]]市建立。<ref name="BigPeachClanton">{{cite web|url=http://www.roadsideamerica.com/story/2014|title=Big Peach Water Tower, Clanton, Alabama|publisher=Roadside America|accessdate=2015-11-20|archive-date=2015-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222052325/http://www.roadsideamerica.com/story/2014|dead-url=no}}</ref>
